<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Wizard Chain-Casting Sunstrike: 170 DPS<BR>Level 60 monk wielding Bo Staff of Trorsmang, hasted 100%, STR 255: 72 DPS<P>Background... Sunstrike, level 60 wiz nuke, does 1615 damage, 7 sec casting time, with standard 2.5 sec refresh... (1615)/(9.5) = 170.<P>Level 60 Monk, 100% haste (36% haste item, and 65% haste from enchanter spell), wielding Bo Staff of Trorsmang (40/35... yes that's correct, not backwards--DAM 40, DEL 35), with STR 255 via Shammy buffs and Übergear: This is, so far, the single most asskickingest damage output that any melee class can be achieve right now, as far as we know from items that have been discovered.<P>A wizard more than DOUBLES the damage-per-second of the best melee in the game wielding Übergear (Trorsmang drops in Veeshan's Peak).<P>Wizards do now and always shall beat a similar-level melee char in DPS. Exceptions to this include the lower levels, against super-twinks (like a lv 5 Shadow Knight wielding an Ebon Mace [19/24] and Sash of the Dragonborn... he'll probably out-damage a lv 12 wizard on a lv 5 monster, probably not on a lv 12 monster though).<P>Anyway, food for thought. Oh, the only true threat to the Wizard DPS crown--the Mage. In fact, pre-49, Mages with pets will almost always out-pace wizard damage. Ice Comet sorta changes things though... bwuahahaha!!!If you want to see a chart, I did a full-out comparison about a year ago, factoring in refresh times, casting times, and pet DPS. I'll post it if I get 2 people interested, hehe...<P>--------------------<P>51 Channeller :: Simryd "Your-target-resisted-Tishan's-Clash" L'Drael, Erudite Wizard of Quellious<BR>44 CLE :: Ulanji, High Elf Cleric of Tunare<BR>30 NEC :: Quokuus Jhuoroq, Human Plaguebringer of Bertoxxulous<BR>24 MNK :: Xodien Lo'Jong, Disciple of the Ashen Order<BR>14 SHD :: Sujata, Iksar Dark Knight of Cazic Thule<BR>12 RNG :: Kujatta, Human Patron of the Stormbringer<BR>*****************<BR>:: "Eschew Obfuscation" ::
</FONT>
