<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
regarding 1h vs. 2h...<P>It depends on the equipment. Basically, there are three phases...<P>Phase 1: level 1 to 30 or so. During this period, most good 2-hand weapons (Xalgoz, Mith 2-hand, Nasthar, Sentry Maul, Adamantite Bo, etc.) will outdamage a pair of 1-handed weapons. The reason: Dual Wield skill is still to low to be of consequence, and the damage bonus hasn't kicked in yet.<P>Phase 2: Level 30 to 50 or so. During this period, Dual Wield skills are increasing, and the added damage bonus from the inherent low delay of most 1-handed weapons means that 1-handed damage output will be better than 2-handed.<P>Phase 3: Überweapons start to enter the picture. Examples--The entire line of Velium weapons from Dragon Necropolis (eg. Tempered Velium Claidhmore (32/35)), also the Tranquil Staff (29/30 effect: 100-point damage stun), Runed Fighter's Staff (19/20), Peacebringer (28/30), Ton Po's Bo Stick of Understanding (44/40), and of course, the Bo Staff of Trorsmang (40/35). All of these will be better than a vast majority of the Über 1-handers. <P>For comparison, the Celestial Fists (monk epic) turn the monk fists into a 14/18 weapon. So, a monk using bare knuckles with the epic is, in effect, dual-wielding 14/18 weapons (for comparison: the warrior epic swords are both 14/24). I've seen several monks compare damage output of epic fists against the Tranquil Staff (2-hander; 29/30). They were nearly identical in damage output. So, take out the 29/30 staff, and sub in a 40/35 staff, and you have the single most damaging melee-dealer on Norrath. If you disagree with that, just go ask any member of FoH or Afterlife what their monks use. Bo Staff of Trorsmang--I guarantee.<P>Anyway...<P>I understand what you're saying, Arlina. The overall DPS from fight-to-fight of any damage-dealing caster will likely be lower than all the melee classes. Such is the price we pay for the speed and immediate power of the nukes.<P>Here's what wizards REALLY are in most XP-hunt groups: <P>- 3rd rate damage dealers over time. (the sticking point everyone obsesses about)<BR>- First rate killers when something needs to die NOW. (don't de-value this)<BR>- Snarers. (PLEASE don't forget this--if you're a wizard and you're the only source of snaring, SNARE by God!)<BR>- Secondary Crowd Control (rooting mezzed mobs so 'chanter doesn't get whacked)<BR>- XP insurance (evac) (this is very important--try averaging the efficiency of a non-evac group that pulls a hair faster with a mage but gets wiped out even once)<BR>- Spell-casting interrupters (stuns--eventually you get many spell interrupting nukes/stuns... lv 20 you get 2, one at 29, 1 at 49, 1 at 51--trust me: preventing that damn seahorse from CH'ing itself HELPS EFFICIENCY)<BR>- Secondary Damage Shield casters (yeah I know it's only 5 points at lv 34, but it adds up)<BR>- Odd bag-o-tricks. Ever try solo-pulling pulling Xalgoz with a full church pop? Wiz can do it, using Bind Sight. Ever try pulling Phinegel Autropos to the zone so CR is easier if you get wiped out? Wiz can do it, using Eye of Zomm and Gate.<P>Wizards rock!<P>--------------------<P>51 Channeller :: Simryd "Your-target-resisted-Tishan's-Clash" L'Drael, Erudite Wizard of Quellious<BR>44 CLE :: Ulanji, High Elf Cleric of Tunare<BR>30 NEC :: Quokuus Jhuoroq, Human Plaguebringer of Bertoxxulous<BR>24 MNK :: Xodien Lo'Jong, Disciple of the Ashen Order<BR>14 SHD :: Sujata, Iksar Dark Knight of Cazic Thule<BR>12 RNG :: Kujatta, Human Patron of the Stormbringer<BR>*****************<BR>:: "Eschew Obfuscation" ::
