To Simryd <P>Ok let have some more fun with DPS.<P>We will use the situation you sugested and compare the monk doing 72DPS ( no misses no reduced damage ), and the wizard using Sun Strike ( with no full or partial resist and no fizzles or interupts and no death do to mob agro from chain casting ).<P>Now I will asume the monk had full buffs, 255 str and uber equipment, and I will assume the wizard has 200 int giving him 2520 mana and he also has clarity II so his regen rate is 39 mana per 6 seconds giving him a regen from oom to FM time of 6 min 24 second.<P>Now my comparison will use your stats under the perfect situation you sugested, in a one hour time frame where fights last 1 min and pull take one min to bring in. We will assume that both the wizard and the monk will start fighting emmediatly untill the mob dies.<P>Wizard<BR>can cast sun strike 6 times in 60 second ( we will ignore the fact that he would actuall by oom after 5 cast and though in the 6th just to make the wiz oom. mana cost would be 6 X 450 = 2700 )<P>The total damage for 6 cast would be 6 X 1615 = 9690dmg<P>The casting time would be 57 seconds.<P>The med time to get back to FM is 6min 27 seconds ( with clarity II on, it would be about 14 min without it )<P>Total time from fist chain cast to next chain cast is 57 sec + 6 min 27 sec = 7 min 24 seconds ( DPS of the wizard is 21.82DPS if you were to use this time )<P>What this means is that the wizard can chain cast 60 min / 7 min 24 sec = 8.11 times. we will though in 1 extra cast of Sun Strike to make up for the 0.11 .<P>So the wizards total damage for one hour would be (8 X 9690) + 1615 = 79135 dmg<P><BR>Now lets do the monk using the 72dps.<P>Now assuming a one min pull time and one min fight time the monk only dose damage every other minut so his total damage per hour would be<P>30 min X 60 sec X 72 dps = 129600 dmg<P>OK let compare total damage over the hour<P>monk = 129600 dmg<BR>wiz =  79135 dmg<P>Now you tell me who will kill more mobs and is more valuable to a group. Is it the wizard who does only 60% of the monks damage under perfect sercomstances and is easily killed, or the monk who can protect other group members, do significantly more damage and can take some real punishment.
