My experiences, regarding evacs...<P>I've probably used evac 15 to 20 times total since I began playing. maybe on 5 or 6 of them, I'd have a group member whine, "we could have survived." It was up to me to point out all the factors involved, and that there was no way on God's Green earth we were going to live, and that I just saved us all a huge headache. I always managed to convince them I was right. Folks just don't pay attention to things sometimes... you have to remind them that it's NOT GOOD that the cleric has 10 mana, and the group just got 2 adds, with the 'chanter at 20 mana and the tanks all under 2 bubbles of health. etc... Yes, it takes good timing to be a good evacuator, but you have to stand up for yourself when you evac--better safe than sorry.<P>I'm about to start another post, focusing on why a wizard is so useful. Rather than hone in on one specific issue, I'll be taking a global view on things.
