Something to add in to this discussion to throw a wrench into it.<P>The damage coming from the Wizard (a Good Wizard) is free damage. No heals, no haste, to str/dex/agil buffs, no hp regen, no stamina refreshing, no damage shields, and all it takes to sustain a wizard is Clarity of some sort, and with luck a Bard. Meanwhile that Monk/Rogue/Tank is out there sucking mana like a Vacume from the Clerics, Shamans, Druids, and Enchanters. Those Melee guys come at a hefty price of downtime for everyone in the party. Sure that monk could sustain constant fighting like that, but only with 2 or 3 people backing him up at the same time. The Wizard is barely noticedable in mana drain on the group. Infact a group with a Wizard would notice an extreme Decrease in downtime compared to adding in any other class.<P>Now put this into your calcutaions:<BR>Single pull safe area both level 60.<P>Monk Solo no buffs no help:<P>Wizard Solo no buffs no help:<P>No way a monk could keep up with the wizard over an hour. They would have way too much downtime for HP's then wizards would for mana. Not only that, the Monk couldn't down the mob before getting their ass literally handed to them in time.<P>Fact is, the Wizard saves everyone time. And we all know EQ isn't about anything else but saving TIME.<P>--------------------<P>Baelzharon Hopeslayer<BR>Wizard of the 54th Book of Power<BR>BANG! BOOM! POOF!, Done! "WTF" you looking at? PULL SOME MORE<BR>Member of <BR> <A HREF="http://www.foreverexiled.net" TARGET=_blank>http://www.foreverexiled.net</A>
