<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
To Baelzharon <P>Regarding wizards speeding up EXP.<P>Wizards never speed up exp, they can speed up one fight but not the rate you get exp. The exp you get is equal to the mobs you kill per hour and the mobs you kill is directly preportional to the damage you do as a group over a one hour time frame. Any tank can do at least 2 times the damage of a wizard over a one hour time frame ( in a group anyway ). This means more mobs are killed and more exp is gained.<P>Regarding Tanks sucking mana from healers and buffers.<P>The only time a tank sucks mana out of a healer is when there is an over pull. In the post 50 game when buffers have realy mana efficent group buffs, they can act as a buffer and nuker; buffer dont go oom from buffing they go oom from nuking ( and they do the nuking job almost as well as a wizard would ).<P>Regarding wizards damage being free and always being FM.<P>Well if you are always FM that is becuase you are only nukeing and being very conservitive ( which you must do inorder to be in any way effective in a post 50 group ). However the pitance of damage you are doing is not speeding up the fight becuase a tank can do the same damage as your best lvl 60 nuke in 33 seconds( how many post lvl 50 fights take less than one min ).<P>Lets use this criteria for an example<P>A tank is doing 50dps ( this is a low estimate for a lvl 60 tank )<P>Lets pretend that you regen mana fast enough that you can cast Sunstrike once per round and never go oom. <P>Wizards damage per round would be 1650<P>Now how long does it take the tank to do 1650 damage<P>Time = 1650 / 50 dps = 33 seconds.<P>OK now lets examing a group with you a healer, a enchanter a buffer, and 2 tanks.<P>Each tank dose 50 dps<P>Assume that the other casters are only supporting tanks and doing no damage.<P>Every fight you cast once and reduce a mobs hp by 1650<P>The average pull has 6000hp<P>once you cast the mobs hp is reduced to 4350.<P>Now the tanks are doing 50dps each that is 100 dps a second.<P>The total fight time would be :<P>Time = 4350 / 100dps = 43.5 seconds.<P><BR>Now lets look at the fight time of the same group using another tank instead of the wizard.<P>group consists of 3 tanks, a healer, and enchanter, and a buffer.<P>Casters only support tanks and do no damage.<P>Average mob pulled had 6000 hp<P>Now you did not cast so the tanks have to do all 6000 hp in damage.<P>Each tank does 50dps for a total of 150dps combined.<P>Time to kill mob is :<P>Time = 6000 / 150dps = 40 seconds.<P>Wow the 3 tanks just kill that mob 3.5 seconds faster than they would have with you and 2 tanks.<P>Now consider the fact that with 3 tanks the damage would be dispersed more evenly between tanks and less healing would be needed, buffers using group spells would have no more mana drain than before, and the enchanter would have one less caster to have to clarity and buff. Kills are now happening faster and all casters become more efficent.<P>I saved the best for last. Becuase the tanks are killing the mobs 3.5 seconds faster with out you the will kill aproximatly 13 mobs for every 12 they would have killed if they had taken the wizard instead of the tank( 43.5seconds times 12kills = 522 seconds, now 522 seconds divided by 40 second per kill = 13 kills ). This means that the whole group is is getting 1.08 times the exp it would have gotten with the wizard in the group.<P>Now no wizard can regen mana fast enough to cast sunstrike ever pull in a group that is pulling constantly. That means every time he is oom he does no damage and decreases the group effiecenty even more than he was in this example ( not to mention the fact that I underestimated the tanks dps significantly, and I gave the wizard credit for full damage and no resist to his sunstrike in this example ).<P>A wizard performing better than his best will always be worse than a below average tank.
</FONT>
