<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Wizards need to be able to do a HUGE amount of damage in a hurry and about equal the damage a melee caster does over time.<P>If they aren't both true (if you have the first you will have the second) then Wizards are not useful to the group.  <P>The fast damage is to give our class their value, their use.  _Every_ caster class has direct damage, in order to be a class that focusses on DD one must be able to stand out and Verant has stated this is the way they want Wizards to.<P>If Wizards cannot contribute enough damage sustained over the time (in short bursts) to equal the damage any other class can put out, then in 99% of the situations (when you don't need that fast burn down) the group is better off with any class that CAN bring that sustained damage.<P>Resistances, fizzles, and aggro also contribute to this need, because a Wizard is uniquely crippled by all three due to the direct need for mana to affect anything.  If a Wizard is limited more than any other caster by these three things they require a manner to contribute that is uniquely compensatory for these lackings.  At present this simply is not so.<P>Wizards blast, stun, AE, evac, root, and snare.  A druid can do every single one of those tasks except stun... and they compensate for that by adding heals, damage shields, buffs, and even debuffs.  Consider how Wizards have ONE stun spell until level 49 and you see a problem, eh?<P>Oh, and Simryd, in 60 levels I evacced 7 times, don't tell me that's so critical, the higher level I got the less people wanted an Evac and the less often it was needed.  Maybe in a group of idiots and Ebayers you will need it a lot but I don't GROUP with idiots.
