Mandingo...<P>Three things<P>First, I don't group with idiots. I do group with an ambitious set of folks who enjoy challenging their limits. This means we do what most groups can't do, and due to the increased risk that goes along with tackling these challenges (like clearing all of HS South Wing, nobody above lv 53), we find we have to evac sometimes. Please don't flame. Just because you don't evac often doesn't mean it's a categorically useless ability. <P>Second... aggro. They should put the following on page 1 of the EQ manual--"If you are going to nuke a monster, wait until it is half dead prior to casting." <P>When both a warrior and a rogue have been working a mob down to half, and you chain cast Ice Comet (or draught or whatever else), you will likely end up dealing the most damage. However, the mob will never jump you. Case-in-point: Rock Golem in the Hole. Has well over 6k hps. I waited until half dead, whipped out 3 Comets, which still didn't kill it. Guess what? It didn't jump me. And I had done majority damage.<P>The insane DPS of wiz nukes is usually important on mobs that need to die, and die now, and we didn't realize it until just now due to a couple of adds. Am I right? So, 2240 damage in 15 seconds isn't fast? 3230 damage in 16.5 seconds isn't fast? okaaaaay...<P>As I've said on this thread and others, Wizards are 3rd-rate damage over time, and 1st-rate speedy damage. But you know what? You could take away the entire line of wizard direct damage spells and they'd still be useful. Remove every last nuke. Guess what? They can still snare. Snaring is 100% mandatory in any group that knows their @ss from a hole in the ground. It is such an important thing, that you could have one member do nothing but that and it would help out immensely. Maybe not in train-central (Karnors) where nobody gives a rat's @ss about playing correctly--oops forgot to snare again and we got 3 adds... "Train to Zone!" Oops, i FD'd right in front of your group--I wonder why those dogs attacked you? But in any real hunting group that goes past zone-camping, snaring is life-or-death proposition. And if your group is going to be ballsy and push deep to challenge it's limits, evac is pretty dang important too.<P>Sure, as a wiz there are some mobs I never nuke. I don't need to. And that's fine. And, as a result, my damage-over-time contribution is smaller than all the melee'rs in my group. Guess what? It doesn't matter to me. And, it doesn't matter to any group that knows everything a wizard can do. If you sub a monk in for a wiz, I would venture to guess that you could pull maybe 3 or 4 more mobs per hour, assuming you had snare covered. This is under controlled circumstances. However... the fact that wizards can root helps the 'chanter immensely at crowd control (which in turn helps the cleric). The fact that they can snare means if you have a group of 5 non-snarers a wizard will help out immensely. The fact that they can evac means you can challenge your limits and push in deeper than you'd otherwise dare.<P>Yadda-yadda... I'm talking in circles now, hehe.<P>Anyway, like I said on another thread... if wizards weren't the 5th most desired class on raids, I might grant you that they are broken. If they offered *nothing* to compensate them for the fact that they are 3rd rate dealers of damage-over-time, I would agree that they are broken. If they couldn't solo faster than any class in the game during some level ranges (quad-kiting anyone?), I might say they were broken.<P>Unbalanced? Yes. Broken? No.<P>Paz.<P>--------------------<P>51 Channeller :: Simryd "Your-target-resisted-Tishan's-Clash" L'Drael, Erudite Wizard of Quellious<BR>44 CLE :: Ulanji, High Elf Cleric of Tunare<BR>30 NEC :: Quokuus Jhuoroq, Human Plaguebringer of Bertoxxulous<BR>24 MNK :: Xodien Lo'Jong, Disciple of the Ashen Order<BR>14 SHD :: Sujata, Iksar Dark Knight of Cazic Thule<BR>12 RNG :: Kujatta, Human Patron of the Stormbringer<BR>*****************<BR>:: "Eschew Obfuscation" ::
