<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Regarding wizards speeding up EXP.<P>Recently I found that I was over estimating the average dps a tank can do. Becuase of this I have reposted this calculation based on the revised dps of the tank. Please note that the results were still in favor of taking a tank for damage over taking a wizard.<P>This is the new criteria based on the dps information I have received recently.<P>A tank is doing 30dps ( this is a low estimate for a lvl 60 tank )<P>Lets pretend that you regen mana fast enough that you can cast Sunstrike once per round and never go oom. <P>Wizards damage per round would be 1650<P>Now how long does it take the tank to do 1650 damage<P>Time = 1650 / 30 dps = 55 seconds.<P>OK now lets examin a group with you a healer, a enchanter a buffer, and 2 tanks.<P>Each tank does 30 dps<P>Assume that the other casters are only supporting tanks and doing no damage.<P>Every fight you cast once and reduce a mobs hp by 1650<P>The average pull has 6000hp<P>once you cast the mobs hp is reduced to 4350.<P>Now the tanks are doing 30dps each that is 60 dps a second.<P>The total fight time would be :<P>Time = 4350 / 60dps = 72.5 seconds.<P><BR>Now lets look at the fight time of the same group using another tank instead of the wizard.<P>group consists of 3 tanks, a healer, and enchanter, and a buffer.<P>Casters only support tanks and do no damage.<P>Average mob pulled had 6000 hp<P>Now you did not cast so the tanks have to do all 6000 hp in damage.<P>Each tank does 30dps for a total of 90dps combined.<P>Time to kill mob is :<P>Time = 6000 / 90dps = 66.7 seconds.<P>With these number the 3 tanks just kill that mob 5.8 seconds ( although the over all fight time is still longer in both cases ) faster than they would have with you and 2 tanks.<P>With 3 tanks the damage would be still be dispersed more evenly between tanks and less healing would be needed, buffers using group spells would still have no more mana drain than before, and the enchanter would still have one less caster to have to clarity and buff. Kills are still happening faster and all casters become more efficent.<P>Becuase the tanks are killing the mobs 5.8 seconds faster with out you the will kill aproximatly 13 mobs for every 12 ( this ratio is exactally the same as before ) they would have killed if they had taken the wizard instead of the tank( 72.5 seconds times 12kills = 870 seconds, now 870 seconds divided by 66.7 second per kill = 13 kills ). This means that the whole group is still getting 1.08 times the exp it would have gotten with the wizard in the group.<P>Once again I will say that the wizard can not keep casting SunStrike ever round but the tank can do more than the 30dps per round with buffs and the right equipment.<P>Becuase of this I still have to say.<P>A wizard performing better than his best will always be worse than a below average tank.
