<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree with 90% of your last 2 posts Mandingo. Without getting into every sub-point, I wanted to mention a couple of things...<P>Regarding a wizard's ability to control what dies and when, you mentioned an enchanter is much better at this. Of course you're right, in one sense. What I was getting at is that it's a 2-part equation--the 'chanter tries to keep everything mezzed (while he has the mana), and the wizard applies the killing nukes faster on the first monsters, and more slowly on the subsequent monsters (or not at all on the last couple) to spread out the spawn.<P>Your point about it not being feasible or even possible in many situations makes sense. So far, I've had relatively good experiences with burning things down fast when needed. Sometimes, like you say, when the monster is far *above* half life, I usually do get aggroed. However, via 'chanter (zero-damage) AE stuns and my own rooots, I can prevent a great deal of the damage to myself when this happens. So for me, the ability to nuke hard and fast remains of value. (my opinion on this may change as i approach 60) Probably less than 20% of fights require this, however. Mainly room-breaks, roamers, and trains.<P>Oh, you may wanna read the necro spell list again.  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> All darkness snares are DoTs. Even the level 4 Clinging Darkness (or lv 15 for SKs) does 30-or-so damage.<P>Your thoughts on the proliferation of twinked melee classes out there are important. This has occurred to me as well (as I've posted, maybe in another thread). I've noticed that there are no mana-regen items (apart from a pathetic few--5 charge clarity rods and the like), but there are several health-regen items. I have noticed that there are items that make tanks more efficient (bad@ss weapons) that you can give to a level 1, but there are no such items for casters--like you say: a spell is a spell. You're totally on the ball here--this is ridiculous. A super-twinked warrior (or SHD, PAL, ROG, MNK, RNG, BRD) is sooooooo much more effective than a super-twinked caster. Not even close. I have a SHD twink, to whom i gave a bunch of Ry'gorr, Tree Weave, Blood Fork, etc... and the differences are simply astounding. I am at least twice as efficient as a mage at my level (15), and probably three times as efficient as a wizard.<P>Anyway, here's to hoping they do something to balance damage-casters.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Paz.<P>--------------------<P>51 Channeller :: Simryd "Your-target-resisted-Tishan's-Clash" L'Drael, Erudite Wizard of Quellious<BR>44 CLE :: Ulanji, High Elf Cleric of Tunare<BR>30 NEC :: Quokuus Jhuoroq, Human Plaguebringer of Bertoxxulous<BR>24 MNK :: Xodien Lo'Jong, Disciple of the Ashen Order<BR>14 SHD :: Sujata, Iksar Dark Knight of Cazic Thule<BR>12 RNG :: Kujatta, Human Patron of the Stormbringer<BR>*****************<BR>:: "Eschew Obfuscation" ::
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
 Posts: <B>30</B>  &nbsp;|&nbsp; IP: <A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_ip&f=7&t=001119&reply_num=000034">Logged</A>
</FONT>
</td></tr>
